	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "According to a narrative in EMML 1840 he was a monastic figure\n                    contemporary to Athanasius of Alexandria. In the same text he is referred to as\n                  \"resembling angels\" (ዘይመስል፡ መላእክት፡) which might suggest an identification\n                with Apollo mentioned in the Coptic Synaxary on the 25th of Bābah." .
